body:
We may be missing some logic to move blackboxes into layer directories if they are only instantiated by that layer. I was seeing a blackbox not show up where I expected it to (in a layer) and golfed this down to the following example:

``` firrtl
FIRRTL version 4.0.0
circuit Foo: %[[
  {
    "class": "firrtl.transforms.BlackBoxInlineAnno",
    "target": "~Foo|Bar",
    "name": "Bar.sv",
    "text": "module Bar();\nendmodule"
  }
]]
  layer A, bind, "A":
  extmodule Bar:
    input a: UInt<1>

  public module Foo:
    input a: UInt<1>

    layerblock A:
      inst bar of Bar
      connect bar.a, a
```

This currently compiles to:

``` verilog
// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.82.0-11-g89749efd8
// external module Bar

module Foo(
  input a
);

endmodule


// ----- 8< ----- FILE "A/layers_Foo_A.sv" ----- 8< -----

// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.82.0-11-g89749efd8
`ifndef layers_Foo_A
`define layers_Foo_A
bind Foo Foo_A a_0 (
  .a (a)
);
`endif // layers_Foo_A

// ----- 8< ----- FILE "A/Foo_A.sv" ----- 8< -----

// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.82.0-11-g89749efd8
module Foo_A(
  input a
);

  Bar bar (
    .a (a)
  );
endmodule


// ----- 8< ----- FILE "./Bar.sv" ----- 8< -----

// Generated by CIRCT firtool-1.82.0-11-g89749efd8
module Bar();
endmodule
// ----- 8< ----- FILE "firrtl_black_box_resource_files.f" ----- 8< -----

./Bar.sv

```

I see `Bar` in `./Bar.sv` and I'd expect to see it in `./A/Bar.sv`.
